Weingarten Realty Investors said it has agreed to purchase 18 shopping centers in the Portland, Ore., area for about $100 million from Portland Fixture Limited Partnership. 

Weingarten Realty, a real estate investment trust, said it will conduct a due-diligence review of the properties during the next 120 days before deciding whether to proceed with the purchase agreement. 

The shopping centers, comprising 1.9 million square feet, are about 95% occupied, the company said.
Weingarten Realty currently owns 105 shopping centers. 

